Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.06,0:01:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}While resting in the bamboo forest, \Nan odd fellow approached me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.58,0:01:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. Are you a traveler?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.47,0:01:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.50,0:01:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you must be heading down the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.95,0:01:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm headed west.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.99,0:02:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what I was hoping... Mind if I joined you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.77,0:02:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.61,0:02:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... I can't seem to find my way \Nout of this bamboo forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.95,0:02:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You must have a terrible sense of direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.40,0:02:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had an awful time...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.51,0:02:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has come through in three years...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.14,0:02:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Three years?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.57,0:02:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. This might sound strange, but I've been stuck here for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.58,0:02:35.59,EP Title BG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2000,0)\p1\blur1}m 0 0 l 950 0 950 100 0 100
Dialogue: 1,0:02:29.58,0:02:35.59,EP Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2100,0)\be1}Inside the Cage
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.18,0:02:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm originally from the village \Nat the foot of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.61,0:02:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you're a local...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.82,0:02:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not as though you can't see the sun, so how can you lose your way?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.73,0:02:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.23,0:02:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I must say, though... this is a huge bamboo forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.78,0:03:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn! We're back to same place again...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.25,0:03:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on? The compass isn't off...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.53,0:03:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We started by heading west.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.21,0:03:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But before we knew it, we were off course...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.41,0:03:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Farther and farther off course until... \Nwe went in a circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.49,0:03:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what happens... You become \Nunable to control where you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.90,0:03:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the heck is going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.73,0:03:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been caught, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.29,0:03:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that it's happened, \Ndo you want to live here with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.29,0:03:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, that's not funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.46,0:03:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? You mean there are others?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.50,0:03:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... A mother and her daughter used to live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.97,0:04:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Kisuke...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.37,0:04:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The mother passed on, but the daughter is now my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.68,0:04:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We're childhood friends, so at least \None good thing came out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.22,0:04:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.23,0:04:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a traveler. We were just talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.33,0:04:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife, Setsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.53,0:04:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.51,0:04:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry about making you keep me company.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.62,0:04:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.93,0:04:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to take a break at our place?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.05,0:04:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No... I'm going to try to figure another way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.16,0:04:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.87,0:04:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, then, take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.63,0:04:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,"Take care"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.85,0:04:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's odd...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.10,0:04:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I made it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.93,0:05:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Good grief...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.36,0:05:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if he's all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.41,0:05:07.17,Alt,,0,0,0,,You never know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.18,0:05:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.17,0:05:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.12,0:05:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you came out from that bamboo forest, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.95,0:05:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.99,0:05:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw a man in there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.83,0:05:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... I wonder if he was putting me on...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.19,0:05:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.86,0:05:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He was captivated by a monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.99,0:05:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lucky you're okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.05,0:05:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.13,0:05:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... There's a white bamboo growing in there, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.01,0:05:36.02,Alt,,0,0,0,,Stop it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.02,0:05:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't tell stories that taint\N our village to outsiders.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.26,0:05:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.99,0:05:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You weren't able to get out?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.79,0:05:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was. But there was something \NI wanted to see, so I came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.94,0:06:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard in the village that there's a white bamboo growing in this forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.68,0:06:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I also heard about you and your wife... a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.89,0:06:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see it, what do you intend to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.71,0:06:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's within the scope of my work, \NI want to ask you the details,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.31,0:06:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,since it's a very rare phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.21,0:06:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps there might be a way to get you out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.49,0:06:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If you tell me not to get involved any further,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.12,0:06:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.34,0:06:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.63,0:06:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides this one, there are four others.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.49,0:06:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... just as I thought, it's a {\i1}Magari-dake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.77,0:06:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,First, can you tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.09,0:07:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,about everything that happened in this bamboo forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.85,0:07:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The kids in the village grew up hearing the story...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.96,0:07:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A young married couple lived in this bamboo forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.37,0:07:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,For many years, the couple could not conceive a child...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.04,0:07:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The husband began to spend time\N away from his depressing home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.18,0:07:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,His wife was a strange woman who talked to plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.55,0:07:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually she began to wander about the bamboo forest night after night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.17,0:07:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then one day, she said she thought she was pregnant...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.68,0:07:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The husband became suspicious of his wife, so one night, he followed her...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.55,0:07:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.20,0:07:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He found his wife enthralled, \Nclinging to a white bamboo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.33,0:07:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The husband was frightened out\N of his wits and ran off,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.23,0:07:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but he returned home after \Nthe villagers admonished him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.41,0:08:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,2894)}There, he found his wife carrying a bamboo shoot as if it were a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.18,0:08:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So she gave birth to a bamboo shoot?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.20,0:08:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they say she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.65,0:08:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't she just have been \Ntrying to annoy her husband?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.94,0:08:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, her husband ran away from the village,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.14,0:08:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so that was what we thought, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.35,0:08:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Also when we actually came to see the "bamboo child",
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.01,0:08:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it looked just like an ordinary girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.38,0:08:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That child was Setsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.86,0:08:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,By then, her mother had died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.94,0:08:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My sister, my friends and I played there a lot, thinking she might be lonely by herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.13,0:08:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But we did sense something strange about Setsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.69,0:08:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,She never ate or drank anything but water and never left the bamboo forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.15,0:08:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, we all still liked Setsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.38,0:08:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But then... One day, we were unable\N to leave the bamboo forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.99,0:09:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We went in circles through the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.41,0:09:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,until gradually, I lost sight of one, then another...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.91,0:09:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I realized I was the only one left behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.90,0:09:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, those who made it back to the village came looking for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.25,0:09:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but if they stayed with me, they were unable to leave the bamboo forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.46,0:09:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought... You knew that, \Nand messed with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.19,0:09:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry... I wondered if it'd happen to an outsider as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.72,0:09:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, I lived at Setsu's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.48,0:09:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Since my little sister was the only relative I had,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.17,0:09:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,villagers fed and took care of both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.33,0:09:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My sister and I were practically \Nraised by everyone in the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.11,0:09:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone was like family... It was a fine village...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.64,0:09:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But after living with Setsu for a while, visits from the villagers decreased...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.50,0:10:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you lonely, Kisuke?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.30,0:10:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.67,0:10:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.41,0:10:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, Setsu became pregnant...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.89,0:10:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,2389)}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.52,0:10:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That was when Setsu's true origin...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.81,0:10:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,...hit me for the first time...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.02,0:10:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The midwife ran off back to the village... and after that, no one ever came here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.78,0:10:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You might find my story hard to believe, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.17,0:10:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it did surprise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.80,0:10:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is this... {\i1}Magari-dake{\i0} that you mentioned?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.05,0:10:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A bamboo in name only, but it's not a plant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.79,0:11:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Bamboos in a bamboo forestall share the same roots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.02,0:11:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Together, they are one, or a family \Nof successive generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.42,0:11:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Magari-dake{\i0} are mushi that live off these roots, posing as one of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.14,0:11:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They grow by sucking nutrients \Nfrom the roots of the bamboo
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.93,0:11:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and in turn, return elements to the roots that make the forest green,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.44,0:11:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,growing the forest and increasing its own numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.77,0:11:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Your wife was born from mushi and a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.30,0:11:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We mushi-shi call them {\i1}oniko.{\i0}\N An extremely rare Mazari-mono...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.43,0:11:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it a bit of a shock?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.10,0:11:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No... Not after seeing what my daughter looked like when she was born...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.25,0:11:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of what her parents were, Setsu is... Setsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.36,0:11:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No one in the village thinks that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.91,0:11:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure they'll understand \Nonce they meet Setsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.89,0:12:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, the three of us might \Nbe able to live in village.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.14,0:12:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So is that why you want to \Nsomehow get out of the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.50,0:12:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.20,0:12:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm also worried about my little sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.07,0:12:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if she's having a hard time because of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.61,0:12:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I have an idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.83,0:12:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I connect all the points where \Nhe abruptly changes directions,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.02,0:12:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it forms an almost perfect circle...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.91,0:12:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You become unable to control where you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.55,0:12:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The center of the circle is... that stalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.64,0:13:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the water that gives you life?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.85,0:13:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.33,0:13:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you share some with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.40,0:13:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry... It's very precious water.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.62,0:13:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother told me never to give it to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.74,0:13:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Even to Kisuke?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.44,0:13:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave him some just once... when we were still children.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.59,0:13:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me... Do you find it difficult \Nto be so loathed by the villagers?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.95,0:13:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yes... But Kisuke and my daughter are all I need...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.03,0:13:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,although I feel sorry for Kisuke because he can't leave...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.81,0:13:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But that... makes me happy...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.60,0:14:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I'll take some...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.45,0:14:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I suspected... I can't get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.73,0:14:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.33,0:14:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that time of the year when the leaves fall...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.89,0:14:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy bamboo is feeding her babies a meal of leaves...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.29,0:14:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the baby bamboos can grow big...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.82,0:14:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Which one is the mommy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.09,0:14:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.87,0:14:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They're raising their children together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.83,0:15:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy thinks about the village come this time of year...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.68,0:15:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's large, with lots of sunshine... A bustling village...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.90,0:15:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to show it to you, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.34,0:15:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be okay, right? I'm sure Kisuke won't leave...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.13,0:15:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Then... you found the cause?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.42,0:15:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Mushi, unlike plants, have their own will.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.25,0:16:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They give commands to each part of their body to carry out their will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.05,0:16:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This mushi's body is this central stalk and the bamboo forest around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.46,0:16:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And the medium that conveys its \Nwill is this water Setsu drinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.14,0:16:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Regular water shows no reaction \Nwhen brought near the stalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.79,0:16:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Simply carrying this water around puts one under this mushi's influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.27,0:16:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, those who drink it, as well. And even those who are near them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.25,0:16:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Today sure is hot! I'm thirsty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.23,0:16:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have a sip.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.32,0:16:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt Setsu knew about it, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.69,0:16:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree... But then, what do we do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.20,0:17:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the problem... If we could get the water completely out of your system...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.17,0:17:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, though, I can't come up with a means.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.73,0:17:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There is... one other method...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.30,0:17:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's one I'd rather not resort to since I don't know what other effects it'll have.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.26,0:17:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I... see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.74,0:17:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I see... If that's the case, I can finally... give up...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.97,0:17:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.62,0:17:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,...who's been keeping Kisuke here for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.39,0:17:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.90,0:17:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.27,0:18:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.49,0:18:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think you can do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.71,0:18:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You're it's child... a part of its body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.31,0:18:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as our limbs can't go against our brains.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.53,0:18:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear everything I said?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.01,0:18:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of me, Kisuke...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.91,0:18:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But Kisuke wasn't unhappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.34,0:18:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Kisuke made a woman like me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.73,0:18:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But I took his village away from him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.01,0:18:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Kisuke even said...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.75,0:19:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of what my parents were, I am me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.70,0:19:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.69,0:19:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Setsu! Where could she have gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.72,0:19:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The village!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.86,0:19:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello! It's me! Kisuke! I was finally able to get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.91,0:19:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.48,0:20:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's me. Have you been well?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.63,0:20:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that... that child?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.80,0:20:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.64,0:20:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.96,0:20:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hear me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.26,0:20:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't come down to the village with that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.19,0:20:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a child of my own now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.60,0:20:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make my child feel miserable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.03,0:20:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Mommy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.91,0:20:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.34,0:20:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.77,0:20:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,For a while, the three of them lived happily together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.28,0:20:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, six months later,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.49,0:20:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,when I returned to see the effects of cutting down the parent stalk...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.60,0:21:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a single {\i1}Magari-dake...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.02,0:21:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.14,0:21:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, the white bamboo wilted \Nand died one after the other...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.83,0:21:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Their lives depended on that water...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.75,0:21:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They suffered greatly...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.44,0:21:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time I buried them here,\Nthey became weak like dead trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.43,0:21:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Setsu shouldn't have done what she did...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.61,0:21:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That was Setsu's parent...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.48,0:21:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I made her do it... Because I could\N never give up the village...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.18,0:22:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already that time of year again...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.51,0:22:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A white bamboo... when did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.60,0:22:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Babies crying...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.25,0:22:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming from... the direction of their graves...
